  "prompt": "What is the Minimum Viable Offer?",
  "response": "A Minimum Viable Offer (MVO) is a concept often used in business and marketing strategies that refers to the most basic version of a product or service that can be offered to customers. It includes the essential features necessary to meet the target market's needs and demonstrate the core value proposition. The MVO allows businesses to test the market with minimal resources and gather feedback to iterate and improve the product or service.\n\nThe key characteristics of an MVO are:\n\n1. **Core Value Proposition**: It addresses the primary pain points or needs of the target market.\n2. **Essential Features**: Includes only the features required to make the product or service functional and valuable.\n3. **Market Testing**: It is used to validate the concept and gather insights from early customers.\n4. **Resource Efficiency**: Developed with minimal resources to avoid unnecessary expenditure.\n\nBy focusing on delivering the Minimum Viable Offer, businesses can reduce the risk of over-investing in unvalidated ideas and improve their chances of success through iterative development and customer feedback.",
